Spent a couple hours with a pen yesterday & brought this little guy out of my head, this hexagonal page measures 2.5" along each edge; within the page there is an explosion of color & geometry meant to be similar to that which I see everywhere in the world around us & my inner universe.
This piece was a little something different for me, it feels strange to work on a page that isn't square/rectangular, but, a few ideas came to mind about how to use shapes like this when I saw the finished product; I'm interested to see what else I can do!

So, those times when you’ve left something hanging out in the sun to dry, like you’ll come back in a couple hours & take it down & it’s got that abrupt-drying crusty crispness (is that a bad thing? dunno...) but whatever. But the thing is, you get busy and forget all about taking this thing down right away, and hours are days & then weeks & then it’s next summer & this thing you left out is all tattered & still hanging but it’s become part of the scenery, part of the surroundings & you think every once in a while you ought to finally take that thing down but you’re a little reluctant & unmotivated somehow... .
So, THIS drawing feels a little bit like that, for me.

I think I'll call this one "You THOUGHT!" As it was a constant reminder that you don't really control the resin. Or I guess, "Resin Art is more of an Art than Science" would be a better way to describe it. .
It was meant to be the milky way, but it turned into a wormhole, then it turned into this, lastly I added COPIOUS AMOUNTS OF GLITTER in hopes that it would make it tolerable. It kind of worked....
.
All colors, dyes, additives, etc are from @justresinart .
I believe it was Indigo, Carbon Black, Ultra Violet, and fine Halo (holographic) glitter.
